 ">full entry</a></span></span></span></div><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="adverse_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late Middle English: from Old French <span class="ei">advers</span>, from Latin <span class="ei">adversus</span> ‘against, opposite’, past participle of <span class="ei">advertere</span>, from <span class="ei">ad-</span> ‘to’ + <span class="ei">vertere</span> ‘to turn’. Compare with <span class="eb">averse</span>.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
